<paragraph blockId="28.[264,937,941,1002]" box="[264,421,976,1002]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
(
<figureCitation box="[273,413,976,1002]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–59" captionStartId="29.[264,382,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[472,1116,442,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-219@29.[462,1124,429,1217]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 57–59. Chrysotimus xuae sp. nov. (male). 57. wing; 58. first flagellomere, lateral view; 59. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048701/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs. 57–59</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[264,1322,1056,1882]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis. Hairs and bristles on thorax brownish. 4 strong dc, acr absent. Fore tarsomere 1 with row of 8–10 v; mid tarsomere 1 with row of 5–6 yellow v; hind tarsomere 1 with 15– 16 erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/4 and row of 7–8 pv. Surstylus on epandrium deeply furcated apically.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[264,1322,1056,1882]" box="[312,1143,1216,1242]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,533,1216,1242]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 1.8–2.0 mm, wing length 
<quantity box="[995,1140,1216,1242]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.9">1.9–2.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[264,1322,1056,1882]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Head metallic green with pale gray pollen; frons and face brilliant. Hairs and bristles on head brown. Ocellar tubercle weak, with 2 very long oc and 2 very short posterior hairs. Lower postocular bristles (including ventral hairs) pale. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1053,1140,1336,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–59" captionStartId="29.[264,382,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[472,1116,442,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-219@29.[462,1124,429,1217]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 57–59. Chrysotimus xuae sp. nov. (male). 57. wing; 58. first flagellomere, lateral view; 59. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048701/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
) blackish; first flagellomere blackish, rather short, about 0.5 times as long as wide; arista subapical, with basal segment very short. Proboscis blackish, with brown hairs; palpus dark brown, with 2 brownish apical bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[264,1322,1056,1882]" lastBlockId="29.[264,1322,284,350]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Thorax metallic green with pale gray pollen, mesonotum and scutellum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on thorax brownish; 4 strong dc, acr absent; scutellum with 2 pairs of bristles. Propleuron with 1 yellow bristle on lower portion. Legs including coxae yellow with all tarsomere 5 brown. Hairs and bristles on legs brownish; fore and mid coxae with yellow hairs and bristles; fore coxa with 2–3 anterior and apical bristles, mid coxa with 1–2 anterior bristles, hind coxa with 1 brownish outer bristle near middle. Fore femur with 1 short av and 1 short pv apically; mid femur with 1 av and 1 pv apically; hind femur with 2 av and 1 pv apically. Mid tibia with 2 ad and 1 pd, apically with 4 bristles; hind tibia with 2 ad and 2 pd, apically with 4 bristles. Fore tarsomere 1 with row of 8–10 v; mid tarsomere 1 with row of 5–6 v; hind tarsomere 1 with 15–16 erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/4 and row of 7–8 pv. Relative lengths of tibia and 5 tarsomeres of legs. LI 3.3: 2.0: 0.8: 0.6: 0.5: 0.4; LII 4.3: 2.5: 1.0: 0.8: 0.4: 0.4; LIII 4.8: 1.9: 1.2: 0.9: 0.5: 0.5.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048701" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5048701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048701/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" startId="29.[264,382,1235,1259]" targetBox="[472,1116,442,1212]" targetPageId="29">
<paragraph blockId="29.[264,1323,1235,1293]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,463,1235,1259]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">FIGURES 57–59.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2005" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[470,662,1236,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xuae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[470,662,1236,1259]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Chrysotimus xuae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[669,753,1236,1259]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 57. wing; 58. first flagellomere, lateral view; 59. genitalia, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="29.[264,1325,1385,1894]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Wing hyaline (
<figureCitation box="[485,572,1385,1411]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–59" captionStartId="29.[264,382,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[472,1116,442,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-219@29.[462,1124,429,1217]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 57–59. Chrysotimus xuae sp. nov. (male). 57. wing; 58. first flagellomere, lateral view; 59. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048701/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
), veins brownish; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[806,837,1398,1415]" fontSize="7" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">4+5</subScript>
and M parallel apically, CuAx ratio 0.28. Squama yellow with pale yellow hairs. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[264,1325,1385,1894]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Abdomen metallic green with pale gray pollen, dorsum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on abdomen brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[264,1325,1385,1894]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[498,588,1548,1574]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–59" captionStartId="29.[264,382,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[472,1116,442,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-219@29.[462,1124,429,1217]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 57–59. Chrysotimus xuae sp. nov. (male). 57. wing; 58. first flagellomere, lateral view; 59. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048701/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). Epandrium about as long as wide, apically with long fingerlike lateral process; surstylus broad, apical part deeply furcated; cercus short and round.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[264,1325,1385,1894]" box="[312,536,1628,1654]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
