<paragraph blockId="29.[264,1325,1385,1894]" box="[312,1290,1788,1814]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Etymology. The specific epithet derives from the name of the collector Yanling Xu.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[264,1325,1385,1894]" lastBlockId="30.[264,1323,284,390]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Comments. This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang and Saigusa" authorityName="Yang and Saigusa" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shennongjianus">
<emphasis box="[809,1149,1828,1853]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Chrysotimus shennongjianus</emphasis>
Yang and Saigusa
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[398,473,1868,1894]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Hubei</collectingRegion>
, but may be separated from the latter by hairs and bristles on thorax brownish, and deep furcated surstylus. In 
<taxonomicName box="[755,974,284,310]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shennongjianus">
<emphasis box="[755,774,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[790,974,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">shennongjianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the hairs and bristles on thorax are yellow, and the surstylus is not furcated (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T." box="[831,1133,324,350]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="155 - 164" refId="ref12011" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T. (2001 a) New and little known species of Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from China (VIII). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 71, 155 - 164." type="journal article" year="2001">Yang and Saigusa, 2001a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
